      "lesson title": "Autonomous Network Operations (Self-Healing Networks)",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson introduces the concept of autonomous network operations and self-healing networks, exploring how modern telecommunications systems can detect, diagnose, and resolve faults without human intervention. While the benefits of automation are significant, including faster response times and reduced operational costs, it is equally important to understand the risks that come with removing human oversight from critical network processes. Learners will examine real-world scenarios where over-automation has led to unintended consequences, such as cascading failures or misdiagnosed faults that worsened network performance. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of how to strike the right balance between automated efficiency and the human judgement needed to keep networks reliable and secure. No prior technical experience is required, as the content is designed to be accessible and practical for those new to the subject.",
