          "slidecontent": "• Fully automated systems can make cascading errors without human checks in place\n• Set clear boundaries for what automation is allowed to fix independently\n• Always keep a human-in-the-loop for high-impact or irreversible network changes\n• Audit automation decisions regularly\n• Log every automated action so engineers can review, learn, and intervene when needed\n• Start with low-risk tasks before expanding automation across critical network functions"
